EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Board of Health to refrain from passing and implementing a regulation restricting the size of sugary drinks sold at food service establishments in New York City.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of youth and community development to review strategies and create a plan of action to protect children who qualify for special immigrant juvenile status.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of youth and community development to review strategies and create a plan of action to protect children who qualify for special immigrant juvenile status.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass and the President to sign the Filipino Veterans Fairness Act of 2011 (H.R. 210), which would grant full benefits to Filipino veterans who fought alongside United States soldiers during World War II.
EventItemMatterName: Filipino Veterans Fairness Act of 2011 (H.R. 210)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign into law, A.0641 and S.4528, an act to amend the Public Authorities Law, in relation to creating a New York City Transit Authority safety advisory panel to study and report on safety from terrorist acts and to provide a moratorium on the closing of token booths and minimum staffing levels on trains operated for passenger service in the New York City transit system.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a NYC Transit Authority safety advisory panel. ( A.0641/S.4528)

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority (“MTA”) to rate stations on the basis of a grading system of A to F utilizing criteria such as cleanliness, standing water, litter, graffiti, rodents, and other pests.
EventItemMatterName: MTA  to rate stations on the basis of a grading system of A to F utilizing criteria such as cleanliness, standing water, litter, graffiti, rodents, and other pests.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of a traffic crash investigation task force.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a traffic crash investigation task force.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the temporary closing of sidewalks.
EventItemMatterName: Temporary closing of sidewalks.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting data about electric bicycles.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting data about electric bicycles.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to periodic interagency roadway safety plans.
EventItemMatterName: Periodic interagency roadway safety plans.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to post certain precinct-related information on the department’s website.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the PD to post certain precinct-related information on the department’s website.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Commissioner of the New York City Police Department to train at least five police officers, including a traffic enforcement officer, in each precinct to conduct thorough investigations of vehicle accidents resulting in serious injuries.
EventItemMatterName: NYPD to train at least 5 police officers, including a traffic enforcement officer, in each precinct to conduct thorough investigations of vehicle accidents resulting in serious injuries.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Commissioner of the New York City Police Department to revise the Department’s patrol guide section regarding police response to motor vehicle accidents that result in death or serious injury likely to result in death to reflect the New York State Vehicle and Traffic Law requirement that police investigate all accidents involving serious physical injury or death, as defined by the Penal Law.
EventItemMatterName: Police investigate all accidents involving serious physical injury or death, as defined by the Penal Law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Commissioner of the New York City Police Department to revise the Department’s patrol guide to ensure that any time a motor vehicle causes a bicyclist to be injured, regardless of whether or not there was contact between the vehicle and bicycle, all of the motor vehicle’s identifying and insurance information is provided to the responding officer and made available to the injured cyclist.
EventItemMatterName: NYPD to revise the Department’s patrol guide to ensure that any time a motor vehicle causes a bicyclist to be injured.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to exempting certain cultural institutions located on property owned by the City from tree replacement requirements.
EventItemMatterName: Exempting certain cultural institutions located on property owned by the City from tree replacement requirements.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance

EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notifying owners of real property about the valuation of real property and requiring income and expense statements from owners of income producing property for real property assessment purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring income and expense statements from owners of income producing property for real property assessment purposes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation to amend the Vehicle and Traffic Law, in relation to requiring the New York State Department of Transportation to reevaluate and review highways, parkways and roadways for safety issues every ten years.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the NYS Department of Transportation to reevaluate and review highways, parkways and roadways for safety issues every ten years.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the New York City Police Department to implement a for-hire vehicle warning alert system.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the NYPD to implement a for-hire vehicle warning alert system.

EventItemMatterName: Required signage informing persons of their right to reasonable accommodations at certain city facilities.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on New York State to require that New York City provide full time pre-kindergarten seats to all eligible New York City children.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would amend the state Public Authorities Law by requiring members of the New York City Water Board to maintain residency in the City of New York, give each Borough President one appointment to the Board, and require that at least one of the Mayor’s appointees be a single-family home owner.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring members of the NYC Water Board to maintain residency in the City of NY.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Assembly to pass A.10291, the New York State Senate to introduce and pass similar legislation, and the Governor to sign such legislation into law, amending the membership of the New York City Water Board to include the five borough presidents, the mayor or a public member appointed by the mayor and a public member appointed by the governor who has experience in the science of water resource development.
EventItemMatterName: Amending the membership of the NYC Water Board. (A.10291)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Public Safety Commission to require utilities to conduct stray voltage testing on all electric facilities accessible to the public every six months and inspection of all electric facilities every two years.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Public Safety Commission to require utilities to conduct stray voltage testing on all electric facilities accessible to the public every 6 months and inspection of all electric facilities every 2 years.
